Review: Drags on and would benefit from some theme subtlety, but stick around for the ending. A chef’s kiss.

I thought it would be fun, and at times it sort of is. The movie is mostly drivel though. Corny dialogue and poor use of Channing T, who showed serious chops with 21 and 22 Jump Street. All his jokes in this come off as cheesy.
Took too long to see this. Pacino reminds us that there was an era before Jack & Jill, he’s fantastic. Fun dialogue and good story, I’ll end up watching this again soon.

Movie: The Worst Person in the World

Review: Maybe the first “one last job” movie.

It’s good action and the haircuts are fun. The three storyline perspectives are kinda exhausting, I almost rewinded to confirm I wasn’t rewatching the same scene. But, all in all worth it for the duel (last one) and it’s a half baked return to gladiator form from Ridley.
